The @nba. @carnegiehall. @nytmag. These are just a few of the household names Bobby C. Martin Jr. has worked with to create enduring branding and visual identity systems. “Redesigning an American institution is absolutely terrifying,” said Bobby, co-founder of the New York branding and design agency @championsdesign. “But it’s also thrilling.”

We spent a day with Bobby, a member of our #BlackDesignVisionaries grant committee, at his East Village studio. Watch to hear about his visionary approach to graphic design. #ShareBlackStories

🎥 : @qledbetter 
Assistant camera: @yukiday
Sound: @philshipmansound

Part I, with ASL interpretation by @harrellmoves ✨ @sirsargent & @kjw speak to @ianspalter, Head of Instagram Japan, and @mayabirdmurphy of @chicagomobilemakers about #BlackDesignVisionaries, onesies and more. "Listening is one of the most important skills for a designer," Ian said. "Learn to listen, to really hear what someone is saying and expressing. That’s how you understand problems more deeply, and it’s how you get to insights that help you come up with more elegant solutions."

#ShareBlackStories

“The tea sets I make are actually very unconventional,” said this self-taught Taiwanese designer. ☕️ His ceramics, made slowly in a spacious Taichung studio, have a raw and contemporary feel. For him, a day of work begins with contemplation. “Usually I’ll start by brewing tea and thinking about what I want to create,” he said. From there, he begins making. Over and over again.
🎥: @anrizzy

node.text: #DesignInMotion 🔵 “Pleasure for the senses.” That’s how @lioncolony (Dave Oh) describes his ASMR videos, which incorporate soothing sounds and colorful visuals to create something infinite and therapeutic. For this playful animation, Dave used a post-modern palette and a series of abstract circles — with a dash of sugar. 🧸 And the sounds? They come from constant experimentation. Dave’s pro tip: “Mix similar-sounding effects to create your own sounds — for example, the sound of an egg cracking can be derived from a plastic bottle!” 🎧

Thomas, who has been photographing architecture for 2 decades, was drawn to this candy-colored stairwell for its pastel hues, narrow banisters and feeling of softness. Thomas found this hypnotizing view during a visit to Leipzig, Germany — a “fascinating old town” that, he said, invites you to explore. 🍬

#GeniusRevealed | When @kai_komics (Machai Humphries) was accepted into the @hiddengeniuspro program, he went in without knowing what to expect. Looking back as an alumnus, Machai said he’s gained brothers, connections and opportunities. "The Hidden Genius Project changed how I think of things — how I go into things and learn," he said. "It changed my perspective of the world."

For the Berkeley High School student, a rising senior who turns 17 this summer, design has “so many layers and subjects.” Looking ahead to college, Machai hopes to continue expressing himself through art, and further develop his interest in drawing, as well as character and logo design. His aunt has been helping him build a collection of his best work, which includes the logos and merch he’s been designing for his school and @hiddengeniuspro. His dream school: @UCLA, where he hopes to major in art and animation. 

📸: @fancybethany

#BlackDesignVisionaries | The Hidden Genius Project is among 3 Black-led organizations we worked with to develop a grant program, in partnership with @brooklynmuseum, focused on uplifting emerging and aspiring Black designers. Apply for a grant at the link in our bio. We’ll tell the stories of our other collaborators — @inneractproject and @chicagomobilemakers — in the weeks to come. #ShareBlackStories

#FrameYourWorld 🌎 Take a break from your weekend and take in this idyllic seascape. With a wide view of neighboring islands in the Mediterranean Sea, Aragonese Castle is located near Ischia, at the northern tip of the Gulf of Naples in Italy. Although it’s a popular tourist destination, @irishdancer1670 (Andrea Klämt) was able to capture a serene moment from inside the castle. Andrea, who lives in Berlin, longs to travel freely again soon. But for now, she finds a sense of tranquility when she looks at this image. 🌅

#OutsideIn 🪴 “I want my home to be filled with life and love,” said @fagusurban (Kristina Kizilboya). Kristina’s plant collection grew organically out of her love for plants, but she decided she didn’t need much other décor if she could create a green, inviting space. 💫

#GeniusRevealed | In 2017, @the_legendary_zach (Zach Braxton) applied to @hiddengeniuspro with the hope of receiving and stipend and a free MacBook. "But it became a pretty life-changing experience," said Zach, now a sophomore at U.C. Santa Cruz. He joined the first cohort of The Hidden Genius Project's Intensive Immersion Program in Richmond, California: 15 months of mentorship, skills workshops, and leadership training to Black male high school students.

As a Genius, Zach was encouraged to pursue his dream of working in game design. "I learned that I could do anything I wanted," he said. On a field trip to the @autodesk office, that encouragement paid off. "I decided not to be extremely shy," he said. After telling a tour guide about his interest in the software company, he landed a meeting with the CEO — and ultimately an internship. Now a sophomore studying game design at @ucsc, Zach keeps one piece of advice from a former @hiddengeniuspro instructor top of mind: "Luck is just opportunity met with the ability to see it. There is always going to be an opportunity; I just need to be observant enough to see it." 📸: @fancybethany

#BlackDesignVisionaries | @hiddengeniuspro, which also has cohorts in Los Angeles and Oakland, is among 3 Black-led organizations we worked with to develop a grant program, in partnership with @brooklynmuseum, focused on uplifting emerging and aspiring Black designers. Apply for a grant at the link in our bio. We’ll tell the stories of our other collaborators — @inneractproject and @chicagomobilemakers — in the weeks to come. #ShareBlackStories
